Fly United to destinations near and far

Choose United Airlines to fly to more than 210 destinations in the U.S. and more than 120 destinations internationally — every day we operate more than 4,500 flights across five continents. Our comprehensive route network means you can book a direct or connecting flight to and from airports all over the world. Our main U.S. hubs are located in the major cities of Chicago, Denver, Houston, New York/Newark, Los Angeles, San Francisco and Washington, D.C.

For travelers on a budget or looking for a quick getaway, we offer Basic Economy — a fare option that gives you the opportunity to enjoy most benefits of United Economy® but at a lower fare with some restrictions. If you need more space to relax or to follow up on work, you can book Economy Plus®. For an experience with additional benefits and amenities, upgrade to United First® or United Business®. If you are unsure about your travel plans, opt for FareLockSM to hold your selected fare, ensuring that your price won’t increase and the flight won’t sell out.

And make the most of your travel by enrolling in MileagePlus, our award-winning frequent flyer program, which lets you earn miles to book United award tickets and more.

On board, take advantage of our inflight Wi-Fi and entertainment system offering movies, TV shows and music videos. On select routes, we provide personal device entertainment, so you can stream shows and movies from our extensive library directly to your personal laptop or mobile device.
